      "to_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "content": "DONE — tmux rename fix + capitalization\n\n**Root cause:** tmux's global `automatic-rename` is ON. After `spawnWorker` called `rename-window`, the running process (shell/claude) caused tmux to automatically overwrite the name back to `developer`. The rename command itself works fine with a pane ID target — the overwrite happened asynchronously after.\n\n**Fix (src/spawn.ts):**\n- Added `execFileSync('tmux', ['set-window-option', '-t', tmuxPane, 'automatic-rename', 'off'])` immediately after the rename call to lock the name in place.\n- Added `const cap = (s: string) => s.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + s.slice(1)` to capitalize the role → `Developer--3` format.\n- Replaced silent `catch { /* best-effort */ }` with `process.stderr.write(...)` to surface future failures.\n\n**Files changed:** `src/spawn.ts` (1 file, ~10 lines changed)\n\n**Build:** `bun run build` → clean (tsc, no errors)\n\n**Verified:** Manually ran the new rename+set-window-option sequence against pane `%95` — window shows `Developer--3` and holds after 1 second (does not revert).",
      "priority": 5,
      "created_at": 1780674859910,
